          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'A GEO score is a composite readiness metric that quantifies how well a website is optimised to earn citations in AI-generated answers. It aggregates individual scores across five weighted dimensions — entity clarity, schema coverage, content extractability, technical AI access, and citation performance — into a single number on a 0–100 scale. A GEO score is diagnostic, not definitive: it converts audit findings into a comparable, trackable figure that makes progress visible and helps teams prioritise the highest-impact improvements first.'
        }
